ISA.Mapping Notes/Rules: The ISA envelope is a fixed length segment with delimiters. Even if a value is not available for any optional field it is padded out to its full length with spaces. ISA is the only fixed length segment in the X12 interchange.

CONSTANT[MPC_OCEAN_SHIPMENT_STATUS].Mapping Notes/Rules: Hard code "MPC_OCEAN_SHIPMENT_STATUS" to target data element

ISA01.Mapping Notes/Rules: Store literal value. (Remove the restriction list of the restriction list of both source and target)

ISA03.Mapping Notes/Rules: Store literal value if present. (Remove the restriction list of the restriction list of both source and target)

ISA05.Mapping Notes/Rules:
Convert from X12 source to canonical target value. Use the X12 envelope party identifier type lookup table to convert and validate that source type is correct.
 
CALL "com.tracelink.contivo.LookUp.XRefCodeLists" for lookup file CL_X12EnvelopePartyType.txt with java. 
 
If source value missing or is not included in list of valid qualifiers, throw error:
 
"Valid X12 interchange party identifier type in ISA05 is required !!!"

ISA06(1).Mapping Notes/Rules: Concatenate converted ISA05 + ":" + ISA06. Trim source of trailing spaces if exist.

ISA06(2).Mapping Notes/Rules:
Concatenate "MPC" + "." + [ISA05] + ":" + [ISA06] + "." + [ISA07] + ":"  + [ISA08]

Note:  ISA05 and ISA07 convert from X12 to canonical, see enum worksheet on Row 24

ISA06(3).Mapping Notes/Rules: Store literal value.  Trim source of trailing spaces if exist.

ISA07.Mapping Notes/Rules:
Convert from X12 source to canonical target value. Use the X12 envelope party identifier type lookup table to convert and validate that source type is correct.
 
CALL "com.tracelink.contivo.LookUp.XRefCodeLists" for lookup file CL_X12EnvelopePartyType.txt with java. 
 
If source value missing or is not included in list of valid qualifiers, throw error:
 
"Valid X12 interchange party identifier type in ISA07 is required !!!"

ISA08(1).Mapping Notes/Rules: Concatenate converted ISA07 + ":" + ISA08. Trim source of trailing spaces if exist.

ISA08(2).Mapping Notes/Rules: Store literal value from source to target. Trim source of trailing spaces if exist.

ISA09.Mapping Notes/Rules: Convert and concatenate from source X12 ISA09 + ISA10 to canonical datetime format YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.nnnZ and store result in target data element.

ISA14.Mapping Notes/Rules:
If source = "0", move "false" to target
If source = "1", move "true" to target

ISA15.Mapping Notes/Rules: Store literal value. (Remove the restriction list of the restriction list of both source and target)

B402.Mapping Notes/Rules:
Store literal value to target if B402 present, Else 

If source missing, map current date time in YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSnnn format.

Note:   When the outbound X12 transform is built, it should *NOT* map this element since the value may be created in IB Transform.
In the unlikely event that a partner does send it in.

U.S. Customs Facilities Information and Resource Management Systems (FIRMS) — Identifies U.S. Customs facilities related to the shipment.
Foreign Trade Zone -  A designated area where goods can be stored without being subject to customs duties.
Port of Embarkation - The port where the cargo is loaded onto the vessel.
Port of Loading - Another term for the port where the cargo is loaded.
Port of Arrival - The port where the cargo arrives in the destination country.
Port of Discharge - The port where the cargo is unloaded from the vessel.
Port of Entry - The port where customs clearance is performed.
Plant - Facility where goods are manufactured or processed
Terminal Cargo Location - The specific terminal within a port where the cargo is handled.
Terminal - Specific terminal facility within a port
Wharf - The dock or quay where the vessel is moored.
Mutually Defined - Custom qualifier defined by trading partners
